---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Superintelligence Relations" description="SiRelations makes human discernment measurable. We help organizations maintain clear, responsible decision-making when working with AI systems that can surpass human cognition.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="badge">Superintelligence Relations</div>
        <h1>
          Can your people still
          <span class="accent-gradient">steer</span>?
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-description">
          AI systems now advise, assist, execute, and shape the context of decisions.
          Regulations require human oversight — but no one measures whether humans
          can actually exercise it. We do.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="/services" class="btn btn-primary">Our services</a>
          <a href="/about" class="btn btn-secondary">Why this matters</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-gradient" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust Badges -->
  <section class="trust-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="trust-badges" role="list">
        <div class="trust-badge" role="listitem">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          <span>GDPR Compliant</span>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-badge" role="listitem">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
          <span>EU AI Act Aligned</span>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-badge" role="listitem">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8-11-8-11-8z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/></svg>
          <span>WCAG 2.1 AA</span>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-badge" role="listitem">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0 1 18 0z"/><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/></svg>
          <span>The Hague, NL</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header text-center reveal">
        <h2>The oversight gap</h2>
        <p class="mt-md">Training gives knowledge. Tooling gives compliance documents. Neither measures whether humans actually steer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-4 mt-xl">
        <article class="card reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Visible Experts</h3>
          <p>AI advisors that analyse beyond PhD-level — and set the standard for what's "rational".</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Personal Assistants</h3>
          <p>Systems that know your triggers, your patterns, your blind spots — better than you do.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Agentic Teams</h3>
          <p>Workflows that don't just advise but execute — blurring the line between human decision and system action.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card reveal reveal-delay-4">
          <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="2" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12"/><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>External Influence</h3>
          <p>AI-driven media, markets, and framing that shape the context before you even start thinking.</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-xl reveal">
        <p class="highlight-text">These four layers operate simultaneously. The question isn't whether they influence decisions — they already do.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Solution -->
  <section class="section why-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="why-grid reveal">
        <div class="why-content">
          <h2>What we measure</h2>
          <p class="mt-md">
            <strong>Discernment</strong> — the capacity to remain clear, responsible, and sovereign
            when working with systems that can surpass you cognitively.
          </p>
          <ul class="why-list mt-lg" role="list">
            <li>
              <span class="check" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
              <span>Where do people defer to AI authority without questioning?</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="check" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
              <span>Where does framing shape conclusions before analysis begins?</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="check" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
              <span>Where has responsibility become diffuse or untraceable?</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="check" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
              <span>Where can concrete checks restore human steering?</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="why-visual">
          <div class="visual-card">
            <div class="stat-number">72h</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Discernment Snapshot</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Regulatory Context -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <h2>Regulatory reality</h2>
        <p class="mt-md">Human oversight is now law. But checking a box isn't the same as having the capacity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="reg-grid mt-xl">
        <article class="reg-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <h3>EU AI Act</h3>
          <p>Article 14 requires humans to "correctly interpret" AI output and decide when to override. Article 4 mandates AI literacy. Both assume a capacity that no one measures.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="reg-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <h3>Dutch FRAIA</h3>
          <p>Impact assessments identify risks before deployment. But they don't test whether the humans doing oversight can actually see what's happening in the interaction.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="reg-card reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <h3>The Gap</h3>
          <p>Compliance asks "do you have oversight?" — SiRelations asks "can the people providing it actually do so?"</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-content text-center reveal">
        <h2>Find out where you stand</h2>
        <p class="mt-md">One decision context. 72 hours. A clear picture of discernment capacity and concrete next steps.</p>
        <a href="/services" class="btn btn-primary mt-lg">See how it works</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .trust-section {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .hero-content {
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .hero-description {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hero-gradient {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    right: 0;
    width: 50%;
    height: 100%;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center right, rgba(30, 58, 95, 0.15) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .grid-4 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .card-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .card h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .highlight-text {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .why-section {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .why-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .why-list {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .why-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .check {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .why-visual {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .visual-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent) 0%, #4f46e5 100%);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 24px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .reg-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .reg-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .reg-card h3 {
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .reg-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .cta-section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .cta-content {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .grid-4 {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-actions {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .grid-4 {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .why-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .why-visual {
      order: -1;
    }

    .reg-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
